                     <interp inst="t18260914-203-person1190" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a gardener, and work for Mr. Challoner, of <placeName id="t18260914-203-crimeloc1166">Neville Lodge, St. John's Park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-203-crimeloc1166" type="placeName" value="Neville Lodge, St. John's Park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-203-crimeloc1166" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-203-off1164 t18260914-203-crimeloc1166"></join>. On the 31st of August, about six o'clock, I was going to unlock the stable door, and saw a piece of wood placed against it, and the mark of a man's shoe on the window; I saw a person looking down from the hay-loft; I said Halloo! he retreated - I unlocked the stable-door, and went in and saw a pair of shoes, which had been on the shelf at night, lying on the floor, and an umbrella, which had been in the coach-house - I looked round and saw a man's leg coming out of the hay-loft window - he jumped down and escaped over the stable wall - I followed a little way, but I knew that was not the person I had seen looking at me; I then went back and saw three planes in the hay-loft, which belonged to Mr. James Beck - I went to the hay and saw one truss higher than the others - I moved it, and found the prisoner there - he was quite a stranger - he said he came to sleep there.</p>
               <p>JAMES BECK. I am a <rs id="t18260914-203-viclabel1167" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-203-victim1189 t18260914-203-viclabel1167"></join>. I had three planes in the coachman's room, next to the hay-loft - I had seen them about a week before.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
